            <scopecontent id="aspace_36237aebfab9125b80d690d2f555a49a">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Series I, Writings, consists of drafts for <title>
                     <part>Country Place</part>
                  </title> (1947), <title>
                     <part>The Street</part>
                  </title> (1946), and a review of Margaret Halsey's book <title>
                     <part>Color Blind</part>
                  </title> (1946). Some of the drafts are hand-written (holograph) and signed, and many of them are heavily corrected. In some cases, draft pages are written on the back of newsletters and governance documents for Negro Women, Inc.</p>
            </scopecontent>
